This paper is primarily focused on deep convolutional networks for visual recognition tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of higher-order representations and non-linear modeling, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel network model, which involves tensor scaling, a technique that is often used in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
